  urldate = {2024-07-09},
  abstract = {Linear fatty alcohols on reaction with chloro/bromo acetic acid in the presence of catalytic amount of p-toluene sulphonic acid monohydrate under solvent-free conditions are converted into alkyl-2-haloacetate which on reaction with Nmethyl pyrrolidine gives ester-functionalized pyrrolidinium surfactants. Thus, new series of ester-functionalized heterocyclic pyrrolidinium head group containing cationic surfactants have been synthesized by green approach via energy saving and cost effective methodology. These new surfactants have been investigated for their surface properties by surface tension, conductivity, and fluorescence method. Surface properties of these surfactants have been found to be far better compared to conventional heterocyclic cationic surfactants having similar hydrophobic alkyl chain length.},
